revision.text:
'''Omuro Kofun Group''' (大室古墳群, Ōmuro Kofungun) is an ancient Kofun complex located in {{ill|Maebashi|ja|前橋市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|12=draft|12=draft}}. Four of the kofun (Kofuns) are designated as {{ill|Historic Sites of Japan|ja|国の史跡|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The group is situated in the southern foothills of {{ill|Mount Akagi|ja|赤城山|12=draft|12=draft}} within the Jōnan area. The complex consists of three large {{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} (keyhole-shaped mounds): {{ill|Maefutago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nakafutago Kofun|ja|中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Ushirofutago Kofun|ja|後二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}. These mounds are believed to have been constructed sequentially from the early 6th century to the late 6th century.
== Main Kofun == * {{ill|Maefutago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Nakafutago Kofun|ja|中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Ushirofutago Kofun|ja|後二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Shofutago Kofun|ja|小二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * Uchibori No. 1 Kofun (M-1) * Uchibori No. 4 Kofun (M-4)
Excavations have revealed additional small round tumuli near Uchibori No. 1 Kofun.
<gallery> File:Maefutago-kofun 2.jpg|Maefutago Kofun File:Nakafutago-kofun 4.jpg|Nakafutago Kofun File:Ushirofutago-kofun 1.jpg|Ushirofutago Kofun File:Shofutago-kofun 1.jpg|Shofutago Kofun File:Uchibori Kofun Group-M1, funkyu.jpg|M-1 Kofun File:M-4-kofun.jpg|M-4 Kofun </gallery>
== Omuro Park == [[File:Omuro Park Toki-no-hiroba.jpg|thumb|Toki-no-Hiroba at Omuro Park]] {{Main|Omuro Park}} The surrounding area of the Omuro Kofun Group has been developed into a park, known as Omuro Park, which is included in the "100 Historic Parks of Japan."
== Cultural Properties == === National Historic Sites === * {{ill|Maefutago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} - Designated on April 8, 1927.<ref>{{ill|National Cultural Properties Database|ja|国指定文化財等データベース|surl=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/527|title=前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}</ref> * {{ill|Nakafutago Kofun|ja|中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} - Designated on April 8, 1927.<ref>{{ill|National Cultural Properties Database|ja|国指定文化財等データベース|surl=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/528|title=中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}</ref> * {{ill|Ushirofutago Kofun|ja|後二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and associated smaller mounds - Designated on April 8, 1927.<ref>{{ill|National Cultural Properties Database|ja|国指定文化財等データベース|surl=https://kunishitei.bunka.go.jp/heritage/detail/401/529|title=後二子古墳ならびに小古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}</ref>
