'''Omuro Kofun Group''' (大室古墳群, Ōmuro Kofungun) is an ancient Kofun complex located in {{ill|Maebashi|ja|前橋市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|12=draft|12=draft}}. Four of the kofun (Kofuns) are designated as {{ill|Historic Sites of Japan|ja|国の史跡|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The group is situated in the southern foothills of {{ill|Mount Akagi|ja|赤城山|12=draft|12=draft}} within the Jōnan area. The complex consists of three large {{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} (keyhole-shaped mounds): {{ill|Maefutago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nakafutago Kofun|ja|中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Ushirofutago Kofun|ja|後二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}. These mounds are believed to have been constructed sequentially from the early 6th century to the late 6th century.
== Main Kofun == * {{ill|Maefutago Kofun|ja|前二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Nakafutago Kofun|ja|中二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Ushirofutago Kofun|ja|後二子古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Shofutago Kofun|ja|小二子古墳|1=Sho Futago Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} * Uchibori No. 1 Kofun (M-1) * Uchibori No. 4 Kofun (M-4)
Excavations have revealed additional small round tumuli near Uchibori No. 1 Kofun.
